<header><h2>Hello, world!</h2></header>
<section>
  <h3>Problem</h3>
  <p>
    As you expected, print <code class="language-cpp">"Hello, world!"</code>.
  </p>
</section>
<section>
  <h3>Solution</h3>
  <p>
    Just do it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Because there is no formatted output,
    <code class="language-cpp">std::puts()</code> will be used instead of
    <code class="language-cpp">std::printf()</code>.
  </p>
</section>
<section>
  <h3>Source Code</h3>
<pre><code class="language-cpp">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;
int main() {
    std::puts("Hello, world!");
}
</code></pre>
</section>
